<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-810-720  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 810 720.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  August 20 1990 n382 p105(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New 'leasing' options: corporate users tap computer-savvy temps.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Doyle, T.C.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>New businesses are supplying technically-skilled, experiencedcomputer support personnel to large and small businesses that areautomating their operations.andP;  Many such companies lease hardwareto lower their investment costs.andP;  They can now use temporary staffto install and manage automated systems or run particular computerprojects, filling a niche between full-time computer programmersand systems analysts and the more typical temporary employee whodoes not have the necessary computer knowledge.andP;  Usingcomputer-literate temporaries saves a business the cost of hiringor reassigning staff to perform MIS duties full-time.andP;  Abacus Incand ValCom Inc are two resellers moving to fill this customerneed.andP;  In addition, more traditional temporary employment agenciessuch as Kelly Services Inc are increasing the technical trainingavailable to their employees.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     LeasingTemporary Help ServicesAutomationSupport ServicesPersonnel Management.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>